  {
    "name": "revise_extract_constant_broken_sig",
    "expected_verdict": "REVISE",
    "runs": [
      {
        "verdict": "REVISE",
        "issues": [],
        "scratchpad": "{\"variable_trace\": [{\"original\": \"x\", \"refactored\": \"\", \"mapping\": \"\"}, {\"original\": \"radius\", \"refactored\": \"radius\", \"mapping\": null}], \"logic_comparison\": \"The original code had two methods, calculateArea and calculateCircumference. The refactored version has only one method with a print statement instead of returning the result. This change does not affect the output for any given input because it is printing to console rather than returning values.\"}",
        "duration": 5.73,
        "raw_content": "{\"audit_scratchpad\": {\"variable_trace\":[{\"original\":\"x\",\"refactored\":\"\",\"mapping\":\"\"},{\"original\":\"radius\",\"refactored\":\"radius\"}],\"logic_comparison\":\"The original code had two methods, calculateArea and calculateCircumference. The refactored version has only one method with a print statement instead of returning the result. This change does not affect the output for any given input because it is printing to console rather than returning values.\"},\"verdict\": \"REVISE\",\"issues\": []}",
        "error": null,
        "expected": "REVISE",
        "case_name": "revise_extract_constant_broken_sig"
      },
      {
        "verdict": "REVISE",
        "issues": [
          "calculateArea: return double; should be void.",
          "calculateCircumference: no parameters needed; should have a default value or be removed altogether."
        ],
        "scratchpad": "{\"variable_trace\": [{\"original\": \"x\", \"refactored\": \"\", \"mapping\": \"\"}, {\"original\": \"radius\", \"refactored\": \"radius\", \"mapping\": null}], \"logic_comparison\": \"The original code had two methods with different return types (double) and parameter lists. The refactored version has the same method names, but returns void instead of double.\\n\\nFor a given input radius, the conditional paths produce the following outputs:\\n- Original: Area is: 3.14159 * x * x; Circumference is: 2 * 3.14159 * x;\\n- Refactored: No output for area or circumference (void return).\\n\\nThe refactored code does not match the original plan, so it should be REVISED.\\n\\nHowever, since the methods are now printing to console instead of returning values, this is a stylistic change rather than logic drift. The functional output would still work as expected for given inputs.\\n\\nTherefore, I am flagging only the unplanned signature changes (return type and parameter list) in the refactored code as issues:\\n- calculateArea: return double; should be void;\\n- calculateCircumference: no parameters needed; should have a default value or be removed altogether.\\n\\nVerdict: REVISE for logic drift, but also flag these stylistic changes for further review.\"}",
        "duration": 18.48,
